g.title: EleanorRank1Convo4 begins.
g.text: EleanorRank1Convo4 begins.

g.title: j2846460385
g.text: What’s it like? Having the freedom to swan about in a city filled with plague and know you’ll never have to worry about catching it?

g.title: j781048172
g.text: "Swan about" isn’t fair, Eleanor.

g.title: j2024756666
g.text: I don’t know I won’t catch it. I just haven’t yet.

g.title: j1027929935
g.text: It’s fantastic. I can help the people in danger.

g.title: j1735212282
g.text: I’ll speak as I like, thank you very much.

g.title: j2664189335
g.text: Oh, come on.

g.title: j3543347026
g.text: Heh. That was Entrati’s whole schtick. Back when he first appeared with the whole ‘Doktor Friday’ medicine show bit.

g.title: j1626313444
g.text: And I’ll tell you when you’re out of line.

g.title: j395998074
g.text: Suit yourself. [End.]

g.title: j468048610
g.text: I’ve seen how you work. You might have been human once, but now you’re Spanglyboots the Space Elf. All spooky light shows and mystic powers.

g.title: j1926239255
g.text: Check boolean EleanorEntrati

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j800563815
g.text: I don’t think you can be killed. Not forever. And I know how hard people have tried.

g.title: j978385988
g.text: Makes one wonder why he never got infected. His family did, after all.

g.title: j1926239255->j978385988
g.text: true

g.title: j819264183
g.text: He managed to protect himself from succumbing, at least. Maybe he’s more like you than you know.

g.title: j1926239255->j819264183
g.text: false

g.title: j1558544717
g.text: Fine. You got me. Sorry.

g.title: j3446283092
g.text: You don’t act scared of the Techrot. Why should you? You have no reason to be.

g.title: j1683104735
g.text: Höllvania’s had a whole bunch of would-be saviours.

g.title: j2241797348
g.text: Eleanor’s being a bitter lemon today.

g.title: j2437796317
g.text: You’re not going to catch it.

g.title: j3680936423
g.text: The Princess, back in the day. Then Entrati. Viktor. My brother, of course. Now you.

g.title: j2613717675
g.text: Sol, I miss the taste of lemons.

g.title: j1616467697
g.text: You don’t know this thing like I do. It evolves. It mutates. It learns. The Orokin thought they could beat it. They never did.

g.title: j3531033907
g.text: Maybe you’re right. But we don’t KNOW.

g.title: j3973558191
g.text: You’re right. I could help people more.

g.title: j3435133852
g.text: Do you see yourself as a hero?

g.title: j881933978
g.text: Something on your mind?

g.title: j946782516
g.text: Have fun with that. [End.]

g.title: j456008439
g.text: Check boolean EleanorOrigin

g.title: j2390958530
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j1421556286
g.text: Boolean EleanorHatesHeroes is now true.

g.title: j3565385647
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j803305336
g.text: Oh Gods, I remember now. Eris. The hulks. The surface of Deimos.

g.title: j456008439->j803305336
g.text: true

g.title: j3412306161
g.text: I keep forgetting we don’t win against the Techrot.

g.title: j456008439->j3412306161
g.text: false

g.title: j2356653806
g.text: I suppose not. And I have no business speculating, really.

g.title: j2765411754
g.text: I’m just trying my best.

g.title: j3207841382
g.text: Yes. I do.

g.title: j2468463590
g.text: No, I don’t.

g.title: j2329757774
g.text: I don’t believe in heroes.

g.title: j1100693396
g.text: Nothing I’d be proud to admit to.

g.title: j2970284232
g.text: It makes what we’re trying to do here feel pointless, almost.

g.title: j2307899773
g.text: It just galls me to see you so above it all, you know?

g.title: j940167697
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j1566549993
g.text: I simply cannot understand how you were trapped in a storybook kingdom and STILL haven’t outgrown that sort of thing.

g.title: j142663288
g.text: +15 Chemistry

g.title: j466717588
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j1683209689
g.text: But thanks for checking in, regardless.

g.title: j3042632252
g.text: Sol. Here I am feeling sorry for myself for being a plague victim, and dumping on you for being immune, and you’ve seen whole worlds get eaten by the selfsame poxy crud.

g.title: j3146226323
g.text: Ignore me. Oozing blemishes are ugly enough. Self-pity is uglier.

g.title: j1780869454
g.text: Good enough. Carry on, soldier.

g.title: j2547198497
g.text: I’m glad. Someone who’s lived as many centuries as you have OUGHT to be a grown-up by now.

g.title: j3103347794
g.text: Good for you. Because I’ve seen what happened when one little boy thought he’d go off on a Hero’s Journey and started thinking of the rest of us as his supporting characters.

g.title: j2430714741
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j862889717
g.text: Boolean EleanorGalvanized is now true.

g.title: j1459319146
g.text: I think I’ll count what blessings I have.
